root="false"><fr:frontmatter><fr:anchor>3631</fr:anchor><fr:taxon>Proof</fr:taxon><fr:addr>#378</fr:addr><fr:route>unstable-378.xml</fr:route><fr:date><fr:year>2024</fr:year><fr:month>1</fr:month><fr:day>31</fr:day></fr:date><fr:authors><fr:author><fr:link
href="jonmsterling.xml"
type="local"
addr="jonmsterling">Jon Sterling</fr:link></fr:author><fr:contributor><fr:link
href="marcelofiore.xml"
type="local"
addr="marcelofiore">Marcelo Fiore</fr:link></fr:contributor></fr:authors><fr:parent>jms-00NF</fr:parent></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter>
 <fr:p>Assume that we <fr:em>do</fr:em> have a <fr:link
href="jms-00M8.xml"
type="local"
addr="jms-00M8">surjection</fr:link> <fr:tex>e \colon  A \twoheadrightarrow \mathcal {P} { \mathopen {} \left ( A \right ) \mathclose {}}</fr:tex>. Consider the subset <fr:tex>U \in \mathcal {P} { \mathopen {} \left ( A \right ) \mathclose {}}</fr:tex> defined below:</fr:p>
 <fr:tex
display="block">   U =  { \mathopen {} \left \{ x \in  A \, \middle \vert \, x \not \in  e { \mathopen {} \left ( x \right ) \mathclose {}} \right \} \mathclose {}}   </fr:tex>

 <fr:p>Because <fr:tex>e \colon  A \twoheadrightarrow \mathcal {P} { \mathopen {} \left ( A \right ) \mathclose {}}</fr:tex> is <fr:link
href="jms-00M8.xml"
type="local"
addr="jms-00M8">surjective</fr:link>, we may find some <fr:tex>a \in  A</fr:tex> such that <fr:tex>e { \mathopen {} \left ( a \right ) \mathclose {}} =U</fr:tex>.</fr:p>

 <fr:p>Thus for each <fr:tex>x \in  A</fr:tex>, we have
 <fr:tex>    x \in  e { \mathopen {} \left ( a \right ) \mathclose {}}      \Longleftrightarrow     x \in  U     \Longleftrightarrow     x \not \in  e { \mathopen {} \left ( x \right ) \mathclose {}}   </fr:tex>. Setting <fr:tex>x:= a</fr:tex>, we have <fr:tex>a \in  e { \mathopen {} \left ( a \right ) \mathclose {}}   \Longleftrightarrow  a \not \in  e { \mathopen {} \left ( a \right ) \mathclose {}}</fr:tex>, a contradiction.</fr:p>
</fr:mainmatter></fr:tree>
 
